executeRemoteCommand

java.lang.String executeRemoteCommand(java.lang.String epicNode,
                                      java.lang.String command,
                                      java.lang.String sessionId,
                                      android.os.Bundle inParameters,
                                      android.os.Bundle outParameters)
                                      throws android.os.RemoteException
Execute a remote command.

Parameters:
epicNode - The node that executes the command
command - The name of the command
sessionId - The sessionId of this command. If null a new command is created.
inParameters - The parameters for the command of null if no parameters are known or needed
outParameters - The parameters that are needed for completion of the next stage of the command. The caller must provide an empty ParameterMap here to receive the necessary parameters.
Returns:
The sessionId of this command. This id is used to later refer to this command.
Throws:
android.os.RemoteException
